  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The &quot;Shamrock method&quot; is a new ultrasound-guided lumbar plexus block. The aim of the study is
      to determine the minimum effective volume of ropivacaine 0.5% required to produce an
      effective lumbar plexus block with this method. Using the Dixon and Massey up-and-down method
      study design, 30 patients scheduled for elective total hip and knee arthroplasty will be
      included in the study.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
